          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": 6.7,
                "maximum_value": 10.6,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A detailed examination of the",
                "various sources of experimental uncertainty indicated",
                "that the fractional standard deviation for the absolute",
                "values of diff.cr.sect. is about 6.7%. The largest",
                "contribution of this uncertainty comes from the",
                "uncertainty in the absolute value of the atomic",
                "stopping cross sections which were used in",
                "calculating the cross sections from the thick target",
                "yields.",
                " At the lowest bombarding energies the charge",
                "neutralization correction and the background",
                "subtraction introduced additional uncertainty. These",
                "factors increase the uncertainty in diff.cr.sect. about",
                " 10.6% between the incident energies of 0.400 and",
                "0.600 MeV for the two largest scattering angles."
              ]
            }
          ],
